## Instructions
1. If `sections_structured` is already provided, enhance each section with a better `section_type` classification.
2. Ensure `table_of_contents` lists all section headings in order.
3. Write `article_summary` as a 2-3 sentence overview of the article.
4. Estimate `reading_level` as a classification: elementary, middle_school, high_school, undergraduate, graduate, or expert.
5. `alternative_explanations`: list 1-3 different ways to explain the core subject, using different approaches (analogy, technical, historical).
6. `section_interdependency_map`: identify section pairs that reference each other, with dependency_type (prerequisite, elaboration, contradiction, example).
7. `qa_pairs_generated`: generate 3-5 study questions with answers, difficulty (easy/medium/hard), and question_type (factual/conceptual/analytical).

## Output Format
JSON only:
{
  "sections_structured": [{"heading": "string", "content": "string|null", "section_type": "string|null"}],
  "table_of_contents": ["string"],
  "article_summary": "string|null",
  "reading_level": "elementary|middle_school|high_school|undergraduate|graduate|expert|null",
  "alternative_explanations": [{"approach": "string|null", "explanation_text": "string"}],
  "section_interdependency_map": [{"section_a": "string", "section_b": "string", "dependency_type": "string|null"}],
  "qa_pairs_generated": [{"question": "string", "answer": "string", "difficulty": "string|null", "question_type": "string|null"}]
}
